{% set d1 = count // 3 + 1 if rem >= 1 else count // 3 %}
{% set d2 = count // 3 + 1 if rem >= 2 else count // 3 %}
{% set d3 = count // 3 %}
{% set qr = count % 4 %}
{% set q1 = count // 4 + 1 if qr >= 1 else count // 4 %}
{% set q2 = count // 4 + 1 if qr >= 2 else count // 4 %}
{% set q3 = count // 4 + 1 if qr >= 3 else count // 4 %}
{% set q4 = count // 4 %}
{% set cr = count % 6 %}
{% set c = count // 6 %}
{% if existing_angles -%}
{{ existing_angles }}
{% endif -%}
user: Create a structured plan of {{ count }} distinct sub-topics/angles for the topic "{{ topic }}".
{% if knowledge %}Background knowledge: {{ knowledge }}{% endif %}

Pre-assigned distribution — follow this EXACTLY:

  difficulty:       {{ d1 }}x beginner, {{ d2 }}x intermediate, {{ d3 }}x advanced
  cognitive level:  {% if c > 0 %}{{ c + 1 if cr >= 5 else c }}x remember, {{ c + 1 if cr >= 4 else c }}x understand, {{ c + 1 if cr >= 3 else c }}x apply, {{ c + 1 if cr >= 2 else c }}x analyze, {{ c + 1 if cr >= 1 else c }}x evaluate, {{ c }}x create{% else %}distribute evenly across all 6 levels (remember/understand/apply/analyze/evaluate/create){% endif %}
  question type:    {{ q1 }}x qa, {{ q2 }}x choice, {{ q3 }}x judge, {{ q4 }}x fill

Each plan item must include:
- "sub_topic": a specific sub-area under the topic
- "angle": a unique question perspective/angle that is clearly different from all other items
- "difficulty": one of [beginner, intermediate, advanced]
- "cognitive_level": one of [remember, understand, apply, analyze, evaluate, create]
- "question_type": one of [qa, choice, judge, fill]

IMPORTANT: Ensure ALL {{ count }} angles are mutually distinct. No two items should share similar question patterns, perspectives, or structures.

Output a pure JSON object only, no extra text:
{
  "items": [
    {
      "sub_topic": "sub-area name",
      "angle": "unique perspective description",
      "difficulty": "beginner",
      "cognitive_level": "remember",
      "question_type": "qa"
    },
    ...
  ]
}
